## Documented Readiness Versus Demonstrated Readiness

Day 92 developed the security awareness training program — the honest year-one assessment (100% completion, demonstrated behavioral effectiveness not yet measured), the phishing simulation program design, and the principle that training completion and behavioral change are different things requiring different measurement mechanisms. The human layer is the highest-priority gap in the current control set because it is the layer that targeted attackers — the threat category elevated by the HC3 briefing — are most likely to exploit.

Day 93 addresses incident response and contingency planning. These two areas are closely related in the OpenMRS program and share a common gap that Day 80's audit readiness section named directly: the difference between documented readiness and demonstrated readiness.

The OpenMRS Incident Response Plan is fully documented (Day 81). The three playbooks cover the three most likely incident scenarios — Compromised Credentials, Ransomware/EC2 Compromise, and OpenMRS Unavailability. The escalation authorities are defined. The HIPAA breach notification workflow is documented. The 2am communication protocol was designed in Day 85.

The gap: IR-3 tabletop exercise has not been executed. POA&M item 004 remains open. Until the tabletop has been conducted — specifically with the 2am/primary-contact-unreachable scenario that the IRP does not fully address — the program has a document, not a capability.

The same gap applies to contingency planning. The CP-2 contingency plan development is AT RISK against its 90-day authorization condition deadline. The clinical downtime procedures exist in draft form; they have not been formally adopted by clinical leadership, and they have not been tested by the clinical staff who would need to execute them.

Day 93 documents the complete incident response and contingency planning section of the capstone, organized around the distinction between what has been built and what has been demonstrated — and what the second-year program needs to do to close the demonstration gap.

